description:
The Trump Administration is elevating a cherry-picked report from Doordash to substantiate their claims that grocery prices are down. The report omits key grocery items from their methodology and inaccurately asserts that the average breakfast grocery costs have dropped over the past year.

We compared Doordash's report to official data on grocery prices. Here's what the numbers actually show.
title: Trump is Using DoorDash to Gaslight You About Grocery Prices

author: More Perfect Union
description:
Texas is facing a water crisis, and a billionaire is trying to cash in on it.
Investor Kyle Bass wants to take 15 billion gallons of water from East Texas area every year, sell it to big cities, and cash in.

But local ranchers are leading a fierce resistance to his scheme.

author: More Perfect Union
description:
Starbucks workers just launched a massive strike in more than 25+ cities, and they're asking customers to show solidarity by NOT shopping at Starbucks during their strike.

92% of unionized Starbucks baristas voted to go on strike. They're demanding a fair union contract with better hours, higher pay, and a resolution to the thousands of unfair labor practice charges they've filed against Starbucks for union-busting.

Workers say that finalizing a fair contract would cost Starbucks less than one typical day of sales.
title: How To Boycott Starbucks
